Sometimes they are inuested by the title of Law it Lawes. selfe; for in such manner it is said Tempore Ed. 1. Fitzh. Grant. 41. Lex est, cuicunque aliquis quid concedit, concedere videtur, & id sine quo res esse non potuit. And so Bracton saith, 9. Hen. 6. 59. b. lay prise pur ley, Que si home plede un plee et preigne un protestation; 
                     Vide 9. Hen. 4. 59. b. Paston. 
                     et puis son plee est troue encounter lay, il naver unque advantage de son protestation. Of which manner speeche there are manifold examples.
